The sawdust popsicle - it's actually called Pykrete. It's closer to 
concrete than ice or just frozen sawdust. The inventor intended it to be 
used to make an unsinkable aircraft carrier during WWII. It also melts very 
slowly due to the low thermal conductivity. It's a very interesting 
material!﻿
